	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
			<p>
				<add>כי מימיני כל אמונו בס"ה</add>
			</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p>
				<addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
			</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Sir!</p>
			<p>You can <sic>precive</sic><add>?</add>, <add>?</add> these few lines<lb/> that some
				of the subscribers,<lb/> have much to say about the prices<lb/> of the Books, and in particular<lb/>
				<persName>Moses Gitzky</persName> the <add>?</add>.<lb/>
				<persName>E. J. Bernheim</persName>, will not take one, on<lb/> account, he wants a
				complete Bible<lb/>
				<sic>wit</sic> English, and <add>לה"ק</add> for a few Dollars.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please to <sic>ansere</sic></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><placeName>Buffalo</placeName>, <date>Wednesday 12th Iyar
					5614</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">
				<date>May 19</date>
			</p>
			<p>in poor imitat<lb/> of German</p>
			<p>Peace etc. to the Master, Sweet Singer of <placeName>Israel</placeName>,
					<persName>Isaac</persName>—</p>
			<p>Most honored friend.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I herewith notify you that the books have happily arrived<lb/> I
				have looked carefully into the account, but I regret<lb/> to notify you that many of
				the subscribers are not<lb/> from this place, as I have already written to you.
				I<lb/> shall gladly take them over, though I have very few<lb/> pupils. Your account
				amounts to $71.—, but my<lb/> order was simply $41.—</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Madam Gostzky</persName> told me, and gave me her<lb/>
				advertisement which is here enclosed, as you<lb/> see. You know that <persName>Mr.
					Asser Friedenberg</persName> does<lb/> not pay anyone. He will take a copy—free.
				I<lb/> however, will not deliver a single Testament<lb/> unless I receive payment
				for it. As soon as<lb/> I have collected the money, you can depend<lb/> upon my
				word, I shall send it to you by<lb/> express. The box has not been opened yet,
				and<lb/> I shall wait till I get word from you what<lb/> to do with the superfluous
				books, in cases</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
			<p>where the subscribers do not reside here.<lb/> Have the goodness to reply to me by
				return<lb/> mail. Also kindly print* for me another copy<lb/> of the Testament and
				also of the Prayer-book<lb/> The first copies were <del>taken</del> stolen from
				me.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please reply,</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Respectfully etc</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">
				<persName role="author">Isaac M. Slatkin</persName>
			</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">
				<persName role="author">Slatkin</persName>
			</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">
				<placeName>23 Commercial St.</placeName>
			</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">
				<placeName>Buffalo, N. Y.</placeName>
			</p>
			<p>I suppose he means name on the cover</p>
			<p rend="The following lines are written sideways at the left side of the page"/>
			<p>P.S. It is possible that I shall pay<lb/> you a visit this summer.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Joseph Ash</persName>, &amp; family</p>
		</body>
	</text>
